A huge outdoor deck offers al fresco dining, lounges, comfortable chairs and a backdrop of towering trees.
A spacious living room features a black leather couch and a TV, and flows seamlessly into the kitchen and dining space.
A master bedroom comes furnished with a plush king bed, hotel-grade linen, air conditioning and wardrobes.
Spend warm days lazing by the spectacular pool that is in the garden and framed by lush green trees and exotic plants.
An additional balcony offers the opportunity to enjoy a cool drink in the warm summer breeze as you gaze over the treetops.
Kitchen facilities include a microwave, oven, fridge, gas stove and all the cooking basics, and a bar top table for two.
A third bedroom can sleep one person in a single bed and has a reading chair, air conditioning and wardrobes.
A contemporary bathroom is decorated in sleek tiles and has a spacious shower, large vanity and a toilet.
A secondary bedroom has a queen bed dressed in high-quality linen, air conditioning and built-in wardrobes.
Rest well knowing that your health and safety is important to us. We clean according to Airbnb's strict cleaning protocol and guidelines.
Our spiffy New Coleman is ALL dolled up to welcome our guests.
Eat in at a cozy spot.
Take your meal outside and enjoy the beautiful view and amazing fresh air.
Take a real cowboy bath in our soaking tub overlooking the beautiful valley.
A nice side table for a coffee maker, ice bucket, etc.
The sweetest of kitchens and a homey dinette table.
The Glampground is located where blue dot is on map.

Want to enjoy a cup of coffee to start your day or take out your laptop and get some work done with our solid Wifi? Whatever you need to get done when you’re at your base camp, you can knock it out here!!

Welcome to Bon Apetite RV at the Styx River Retreat & Campground!! Rent a tube or a kayak after a busy day down at the beach down in Gulf Shores- this location provides the best of both worlds, right off I-10, it’s still with 45 minutes of the beach
2 full size bunk beds..... make sure to give a boost to whoever ends up staying in the top bunk!!
Full kitchen includes all the amenities you would expect, stove, premium faucet & 2 sided sink, microwave, full-size fridge and freezer, & all the utensils, silverware, pots and pans you need
Simple couch allows you to take your shoes off after a busy day and watch the TV in the living room that only has broadcast TV stations on it in HD

Full bathroom in the RV if you need a place to quickly take care of your business at night when it’s not convenient to get to the larger Campground bathrooms... we recommend to use the Campground facilities since the black tank is only emptied weekly
This is your home away from home, a nice shade tree and outdoor picnic table give you even more room to relax and stretch out....
In the master bedroom we have a 32” inch smart wifi tv and a nice 9” metal fan for those that enjoy the sound of a fan at night and constant air blowing on you....

Want to make some bacon and eggs for breakfast? Why not do it in the comfort of your own lodging? We always have a lighter to light the propane eyes here and necessary pots, pans, and utensils you need to cook and eat!!
Fully stocked coffee maker and items to make coffee here... always helps to start your day off right....
A microwave is a basic necessity anywhere you stay!!
Almost a full sized fridge to keep leftovers or your milk and other beverages cold!!
Sometimes you just want ice on standby or an easy microwaveable meal.... we can help you there with our freezer!!
An idea of the decor next to the dining area..
Bluetooth enabled stereo .... just hold the Bluetooth button and search for DV1100 on your phone.... passcode is an easy “0000”
An adjustable thermostat makes your stay even more enjoyable.... when you aren’t there we request you leave it at 76 degrees...
A toaster oven is far easier to operate than a propane powered oven.... if you want to bake, we prefer you use this instead of the oven...
The short hallway from the living room to the master bedroom
Another view of the outside of the RV
An idea of the space between the dining room table and the kitchen... the brown door is where the bathroom is..
Another view of the kitchen area
Another angle of the bathroom area
The shower area and decor over the toilet
3 towel hooks in the bathroom area and 2 towel hooks in the master bedroom area...
Fully stocked with plates, bowls, cups, coffee mugs, & 2 wine glasses
You are located at camper spot #8
Charcoal grill and picnic tables by the river
The general store also has bags of ice, tube rentals and kayaks available....
Blue swing under the oak tree is about 150 ft from this campsite
The main sign you see when you turn right down the black gravel road to get to the campground...
Washer and dryers on site that you can use credit cards to do your laundry
RV bathrooms have full size toilets and shower facilities.... 4 total...
Another view of the public toilets at the campground bathrooms
An example of the WiFi speed at the campground
There also tent sites on this campground so you will see other families but they are more than 300 feet away from you....
The renown Styx river, perfect for swimming, floating, or kayaking any time of the year!!
The large covered pavilion is called “The Hangout”.... sometimes you might want to get away from your group but still be out of the sun or rain and this is the place to go!!
During the fall + winter months the queen size bed is made with a fitted sheet, top sheet, and four blankets (including a Pendleton wool blanket on top)
During summer months the bed has a fitted sheet, top sheet, and quilt.
Battery operated lantern on either side  of the bed
Inside the tent we have an electric kettle, French press, coffee + teas, an electric heater, and picnic basket

Picnic basket with service for two.
[Plates, knives, forks, spoons, mugs, bottle opener, and salt + pepper shakers]
32oz refillable glass water bottle with handle, glasses, french press, mugs, coffee + teas, and creamers
String lights with 8 different settings to choose from.
Each campsite is equipped with its own private fire pit
Or use the cookout tripod for your meals
Use the dutch oven or grill directly over the fire pit

Kitchen area available
(The wind sometimes blows the dishes about so there are dishes inside the picnic basket in your tent as well)
You get to adjust the heating and cooling unit to your liking through night or day! The roof is doubly insulated to help you stay comfortable.
I love Black Susans and since they’re part of our beautiful landscape around the tent- they get to part of our Glamping on Hampton logo

Your space to hang out for the time you’re here! The lightening bugs come alive at night as well as the string lights above the patio. You can enjoy an evening outside under the stars in our quiet neighborhood

Cozy living room where you can play chess, sequence, read a book, or grab some popcorn from our local Dutch Kernel store and curl up and watch a movie of your choice connected through fire stick and our unlimited WiFi
Enjoy cooking your favorite foods in any of the pots,pans, griddle, toaster oven or outside over the grill which burns wood or coal!
Enjoy all the luxuries of this bathroom with a shower, urinal, and even a dry flush toilet!! You would never know you’re staying in a TENT!!
Wash cloths,towels, & q-tips, available for you as well as a couple books while you spend time in this room!!:)
Tiny Closet in both bedrooms available for your clothes
When it’s warm and sunny outside ,you can enlarge your space by opening both the screen and the tent flap, and allow the fresh breeze to waft through the tent

Enjoy sitting around this table with your friends and your favorite drinks! 

If it’s chilly, make sure you keep the tent closed and zipped to contain all the heat possible for your comfort.
Always pack your swimsuits in case you want to enjoy the hottub! Always clean! Always hot and ready just for you!!
Don’t forget to bring all the goodies to make your favorite s’mores !!
From the fire pit- you can enjoy the most beautiful sunsets!!

Eco friendly.

Glamping Eco Spirit is a personalized travel agency, focused on sustainable tourism and committed to working with communities to improve their quality of life, while continuing to safeguard the environment. Aimed at tourists responsible for the environment who are more directly and participatively involved in a sustainable way; interested in reducing the greenhouse effect gases caused by your trip, accompanying holidayers focused on a better understanding of nature from an eco-friendly point of view, with respect to the natural environment and its population. In that sense, we work with rural communities that truly care for their nature.

Very few people really know how to contribute to nature in each adventure, with that understanding Glamping Eco Spirit puts its facilities and activities at the service of true travelers who know that environmental care is essential and thus maintain a constant balance that cannot be altered.

Glamping Eco Spirit, uses its knowledge to contribute to the environment, motivating the development of responsible and sustainable tourism from the realization of good practices, remember that the world in which you live not only belongs to you, take care of it for others and others will learn to care for you, a change begins when we do not expect it, but we provoke it.

Eco amigable.

Glamping Eco Spirit es una agencia de viajes personalizada, enfocada en el turismo sostenible tiene el compromiso de trabajar mutuamente con las comunidades para que mejoren su calidad de vida, sin dejar de salvaguardar el medio ambiente. Dirigida a turistas responsables por el medio ambiente que se involucren de manera más directa y participativa de forma sostenible; interesados en reducir los gases efecto invernaderos que causa su viaje, acompañando en vacaciones orientadas a un mejor entendimiento de la naturaleza desde un punto de vista eco amigable, con respeto al ambiente natural y su población. En ese sentido, trabajamos con comunidades rurales que cuidan verdaderamente su naturaleza.

Muy pocas personas conocen realmente como contribuir a la naturaleza en cada aventura, en ese entender Glamping Eco Spirit pone al servicio sus instalaciones y actividades a los verdaderos viajeros quienes saben que es indispensable el cuidado del medio ambiente y así mantener un constante balance que no puede ser alterado.

Glamping Eco Spirit, utiliza sus conocimientos para contribuir al entorno, motiva el desarrollo de un turismo responsable y sostenible a partir de la realización de buenas prácticas, recuerda que el mundo en el que te mueves no solo te pertenece a ti, cuídalo para los demás y los demás aprenderán a cuidarlo para ti, un cambio comienza cuando no lo esperamos, sino que lo provocamos.

BUCKAROO BUNK HOUSE provides a uniquely fun lodging opportunity for young guests and guests young at heart... for buckaroos willing to forgo some creature comforts, yet still enjoy the basics: a roof over their heads, comfy beds and a warm campfire.

A pair of bunk beds sleep two people. Bring your own sleeping bags - OR - we can provide bedding. You will be provided with towels, a coffee maker, and you will have access to a microwave oven and water.

Good quality 10" thick AIR MATTRESSES provide comfortably firm bedding for the bunks. Naturally they are NOT for large or extra large individuals, and we would recommend that those buckaroos find lodging with more conventional and suitable bedding.

The bunk house is 9x12 ft, and enjoys electricity for recharging your phones and making coffee. It does not, however, have plumbing. Buckaroos will use a nearby "clean" outhouse or, for the less game and hardy, you will share the in-house bathroom.
Bunk House guests may meet other guests enjoying our High Meadow property. Nearby is a 1954 vintage canned ham camper trailer, and a little farther away is a small campsite.
Buckaroo Bunk House guests will be amused by some of the Old West accessories, such as a stuffed Armadillo, cowboy boots, and Louis Lamour novels.
For game and hardy buckaroos, an ancient and venerable fully functioning funky outhouse is located nearby.
One of our guests revealed that she so loved the forested outhouse with its airy screened window that she just wanted to sit there all day! (And, NO, I did not make that up!!!)
A simple storage pod is located next to the Bunk House. It stores the hosts personal items and is not open to guests.
The kumbaya communal campfire ring is a favorite gathering place for evening chitchat, telling yarns, maybe some singing and playing music, and... be prepared to share your favorite bad joke as well.

Wood burning fires are permitted for most of the year. However, our Island County Fire Marshall typicall restricts open fires in late summer and fall.  For thos times, we do have a permissable outdoor propane firepit.

Your AIRBNB hosts live in their home located about 100ft from the Bunk House and campfire. Bunk house guests may use a shared bathroom in the ground level of the home. It includes a sink, toilet and shower. Hosts provide towels, soap and shampoo.

Hosts lived in-town Langley for 20 years, but in Dec 2019 they moved to this 2 acre High Meadow property. The contemporary craftsman style home was custom built in 1976. Hosts are close enough to be accessible,  but far away enough away for privacy.
A small RV campsite is also located on our property. These guests would share the campfire ring.
